# Integration Test Cycle - Minimal context, explore as needed
#
# Server: /home/bewest/src/worktrees/nightscout/cgm-pr-8447 (localhost:1337)
# Tools:  tools/swift-nightscout-tests/, tools/kotlin-nightscout-tests/
# Focus:  REQ-SYNC-072 (Option G), GAP-TREAT-012 (treatments), GAP-SYNC-045 (entries)

MODEL claude-sonnet-4-20250514
ADAPTER copilot
MODE development
CONTEXT-LIMIT 50%
ON-CONTEXT-LIMIT compact
COMPACT-PRESERVE selected-task build-errors test-failures

RUN-ON-ERROR continue
RUN-OUTPUT-LIMIT 5K
RUN-TIMEOUT 120s
ALLOW-SHELL true

# === Phase 0: Quick Check ===
ELIDE
RUN git status -s && curl -s localhost:1337/api/v1/status.json | head -1 || echo "Server not running"
ELIDE

PROMPT Check git status and server. If server down, see `docs/backlogs/README.md` for start instructions.

# === Phase 1: Select Task ===
ELIDE
RUN grep -E "^## 🔴|^\| \`uuid-fix" docs/backlogs/README.md | head -15
ELIDE

PROMPT Pick a ready work item (📋 Ready). The active work is UUID_HANDLING scope correction:
- `docs/backlogs/uuid-identifier-lookup.md` - Full spec and work items
- `docs/backlogs/README.md` - Quick reference

State: `Selected: [ID] - [description]`

# === Phase 2: Execute ===
PROMPT Execute task. Explore source code as needed:
- Loop: `externals/LoopWorkspace/`
- AAPS: `externals/AndroidAPS/`
- NS API: `/home/bewest/src/worktrees/nightscout/cgm-pr-8447/lib/`

Build tools: `swift build` or `./gradlew build` in tools/ dirs.

# === Phase 3: Verify ===
ELIDE
RUN cd tools/swift-nightscout-tests && swift build 2>&1 | tail -5 || true
ELIDE
RUN cd /home/bewest/src/worktrees/nightscout/cgm-pr-8447 && npm test -- --grep "UUID" 2>&1 | grep -E "passing|failing" || true
ELIDE

PROMPT Verify builds pass. Fix errors before proceeding.

# === Phase 4: Update & Commit ===
PROMPT Update backlog task status. Commit with trace refs.

ELIDE
RUN git status -s
ELIDE

# === Done ===
PROMPT Summary: Task, commit hash, test results. Check `docs/backlogs/README.md` for next task.
